    <label>506004 Transmitter Flush-Mounted 4-Gang Switch</label>
    <description>Transmitter Flush-Mounted 4-Gang Switch&lt;br /&gt&lt;h1&gtOverview&lt;/h1&gt&lt;p&gtThe flush-mounted transmitter is a battery-powered radio transmitter to which you can connect up to four make contacts (e.g. push-buttons)&lt;/p&gt &lt;p&gtLine pairs are:&lt;/p&gt &lt;ul&gt&lt;li&gtred/white-red: Input E1&lt;/li&gt &lt;li&gtgreen/white-green: Input E2&lt;/li&gt &lt;li&gtbrown/white-brown: Input E3&lt;/li&gt &lt;li&gtblue/white-blue: Input E4&lt;/li&gt &lt;/ul&gt&lt;p&gt&lt;strong&gtAttention:&lt;/strong&gt The flush-mounted transmitter can be damaged. Never connect the flush mounted transmitter to 230 V&lt;/p&gt &lt;br /&gt&lt;h2&gtInclusion Information&lt;/h2&gt&lt;p&gtTriple click on operating surface of a connected switch&lt;/p&gt &lt;br /&gt&lt;h2&gtExclusion Information&lt;/h2&gt&lt;p&gtTriple click on operating surface of a connected switch&lt;/p&gt &lt;br /&gt&lt;h2&gtWakeup Information&lt;/h2&gt&lt;p&gtTriple click on operating surface of a connected switch.Â Wait until the LED goes out.&lt;/p&gt</description>
